records.addlTxt: Case Called @ 1:08 PM: Defendant Victor Nava in court with attorney Jeanne L. Zamzow.  Steven Paul Anderson appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Per Atty Zamzow:  Agreement reached with argued terms on sentencing.    Complaint Stated - Advised of offense and minimum/maximum penalty.  Receipt Admitted - Reading Waived.  Preliminary Hearing and Time Limits discussed.  Defendant wishes to waive preliminary hearing.  Court questions defendant and accepts waiver of preliminary hearing.  The Court finds probable cause that a felony offense occurred within the Court's jurisdiction as to Count No 1.  Def BOT.  INFO Filed - Receipt Admitted - Reading Waived. Terms of bifurcated SEH explained.    Defendant advised of minimum/maximum penalty.  Plea QN reviewed w/Defendant.  Plea colloquy entertained.  Collateral consequences explained. Chapter 950 compliance addressed.  Plea Ct No 1:  NC   Court accepts plea and enters JOC.  Argument by ADA - 60 days WCJ.  Argument by Atty Zamzow - 30 days WCJ.  Statement by Def:   Yes.  Def confirms that he has declined probation.  The Court:  Accepts recommendation for 60 days WCJ as appropriate sentence.  Expresses the Court's wishes to place Def on probation.  Honors Def's right to decline supervision.  Report:  6/1/2015 at 8:00 PM.  No authority to order SEH served in another jurisdiction, however will not object if arrangements can be made.  GT and Huber Privileges granted as Direct Sentence.  No TS credit.  Court Costs - 60 DTP or PP.  Appeal Rights Given.

The defendant must maintain absolute sobriety, may not be present upon the premises of any bars, and is prohibited from possessing/ingesting any impairing substances that have not been prescribed by a physician.    Complete ID process with the Sheriff's Department.

Case Called @ 1:15 PM: Defendant Victor Nava in court.  Scott C. Blader appeared for the State of Wisconsin.   Complaint Stated - Advised of offense and minimum/maximum penalty.  Receipt Admitted - Reading Waived.  Def advised of right to cousel.  Def requests continuance on seeking counsel.  Def employed and resides in Dane Co.  Def expects to have counsel by the end of the month.  AIA Scheduled - NOH Given.  Court enters Riverside Ruling in favor of the State.  Court orders $1000 Signature Bond as requested by the State.
